    <!-- Latest News Begin -->
    <section class="latest spad">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-8 col-md-8 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="section-title">
                        <span>Our News</span>
                        <h2>Wound care tips</h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="latest__item">
                        <h5><a href="#">Gently Clean the Wound</a></h5>
                        <p>
                            For acute wounds, clean the wound with mild soap and warm water. For chronic wounds, use a saline solution or as directed by your healthcare provider.
                            Avoid Harsh Solutions: Avoid using hydrogen peroxide, alcohol, or strong antiseptics as they can damage healthy tissue.
                        </p>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="latest__item">
                        <h5><a href="#">Eat Well</a></h5>
                        <p>Maintain a balanced diet with adequate protein, vitamins, and minerals. Proper nutrition is essential for wound healing.</p>
                       
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="latest__item">
                        <h5><a href="#">Avoid Picking or Scratching</a></h5>
                        <p>Do not pick at scabs or attempt to remove any embedded objects (e.g., splinters). This can introduce bacteria.</p>
                       
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="latest__item">
                        <h5><a href="#"</a> Antibiotics</h5>
                        <p>If prescribed antibiotics, take the full course as directed, even if the wound starts to feel better.</p>
                       
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
